the insane is now the subject of an extraordinary exhibition at the
Drawing Center in SoHo. The collection consists primarily of
drawings and paintings on paper gathered during the early decades
of this century from asylums in Germany, Switzerland and Austria by
doctors at a psychiatric clinic at the University of Heidelberg. By
Roberta Smith.
