to wear a feather boa around the Senate sometimes.'' (McCain on his
resemblance to Ventura, Associated Press, April 17) &QL;   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LAWSUIT OF THE WEEK: &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   George W. Bush has been named as defendant in a lawsuit against
the Texas Funeral Service Commission. Its former executive
director, Eliza May, claims she was fired by the state for
repeatedly reporting violations by Service Corporation
International, the world's largest funeral company. SCI, which is
based in Houston, gave money to Bush's 1998 gubernatorial campaign.
(Salon, April 18) &QL;   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INCENTIVE OF THE WEEK: &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``It would be like a bunch of investors in your industry saying,
Well, let's get rid of the team that made `American Beauty' and get
the ones that made `Howard the Duck.''' (Al Gore on why you
shouldn't vote Republican. He was addressing a $25,000-a-head
dinner, organized by Jeffrey Katzenberg _ the mogul behind ``Howard
the Duck.'' Washington Post, April 17) &QL;   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CANDIDATE 2004: &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Newt Gingrich, former speaker of the House, declared that
Hillary Rodham Clinton would beat Rudy Giuliani in the battle for
New York's Senate seat and, if Gore loses the presidency this year,
she would head the Democratic ticket in 2004. &QL;   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IT'S BEEN DOWNHILL SINCE...: &LR;  &QL;
