<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 10:40 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3246 &Cx1f; tad-z
r a BC-WARNER-ON-WOOD22-COX     04-21 0471
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WARNER-ON-WOOD22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Big brother tool may be watching
 &HT;    By Jack Warner
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ While nosing around on the Internet the other day, I
came across a Web site that will delight woodworkers who have a
sense of humor, especially woodworkers with a sense of humor who
feel the demonizing of firearms has gone too far.
</P>
<P>
   The site, called Mothers Insisting on Licensed Tools, can be
reached via http://www.frenchu.com/tpg/drill.html, and is quite
large for a spoof site.
</P>
<P>
   The remarkable thing about it, once you start reading the many
entries, is that it's really straightforward; it just puts a nasty
spin on tools.
</P>
<P>
   There is, for instance, a picture of a standard half-inch drill
labeled ``The Assault Drill,'' with arrows pointing to its features
_ it's a .50 caliber tool, it has not one but two pistol grips, can
be set for full automatic and with the right bit, it's
armor-piercing.
</P>
<P>
   Even worse is the Milwaukee Sawsall, a standard reciprocating
saw.
</P>
<P>
   ``This industrial monster not only has NO child safety features
to prevent young hands from starting it, but it also has a giant
blade with sharp teeth fully exposed with no guards of any kind!
</P>
<P>
   ``When we at MILT saw one of these monsters, all we could do was
murmur to each other that if we had set out to design a tool for
the sole purpose of maiming children, this is what it would look
like. A 10-amp motor and over 3,000 strokes per minute _ My God,
what are these people thinking?
</P>
<P>
   ``Who needs that kind of cutting power? Can you imagine how
quickly the delicate wrists or neck of your toddler would surrender
to this reciprocating Blade of Death?''
</P>
<P>
   Nonetheless, MILT reported, hardware stores are routinely
selling these machines to children, no questions asked.
</P>
<P>
   MILT sponsors tool buy-back programs, presents an assortment of
occasionally gruesome Biblical quotes to show that tools are
anathema, and, best of all, presents case studies under the heading
of True Tool Crimes.
</P>
<P>
   Homicides employing tools other than firearms or knives are not
at all uncommon, of course, but some of these are priceless in
their descriptions.
</P>
<P>
   From the Manchester Guardian:
</P>
<P>
   ``... Holleran told psychiatrists that Mr. Stephenson had
criticised him for not lifting the seat when he went to the toilet,
and had hit him on the chin ... Holleran had then fetched the
hammer and hit his landlord as he sat in an armchair (killing him).
</P>
<P>
   ``Holleran left and joined a Christian sect in Northampton.''
</P>
<P>
   I think we had all better catch up on our dues to the National
Tool Users Association. You know how it works. First they'll come
for our table saws, and they won't be satisfied until they've taken
our chisels, too.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
