<P>
   RUSSIA-U.S.-ARMS (Moscow) The Russian Parliament approved the
nuclear test-ban treaty Friday, a week after approving the START II
arms reduction treaty. The U.S. has not yet ratified the treaty. By
Patrick E. Tyler.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-CHECHNYA (Moscow) _ President-elect Vladimir Putin said
he had swapped peace proposals with the Chechen president, Aslan
Maskhadov. Maskhadov, in an interview published Friday, said he had
ordered a cease-fire. By Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-CONGO (Victoria Falls, Zimbabwe) _ The presidents of
Zimbabwe, Uganda and Namibia met with other African leaders Friday
to discuss the war in Congo and various regional issues. By Henri
E. Cauvin.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-RUSSIA (Tokyo) _ The Russian coast guard fired on and
seized a Japanese fishing boat Friday in waters near the
northernmost main island of Japan, according to Japanese and
Russian officials. By Howard W. French.
</P>
<P>
   ITALY-POLITICS (Rome) _ The formation of new center-left
government, with Treasury Minister Giuliano Amato as prime
minister, seemed likely Friday. By Alessandra Stanley.
