asylum on his own, what exactly are the precedents for a court's
listening to a child as young as 6? By William Glaberson.
</P>
<P>
   DEATHROW-TERRELL (Houston, Texas) _ A profile of Charles
Terrell, a former corrections commissioner for whom Texas' very
active death row facility is named. By Jim Yardley.
</P>
<P>
   U.S.-CATHOLICS-VIETNAM (New Orleans) _ Major changes in
immigration law, together with political and economic upheavals
around the world, have brought to the United States an influx of
Latin Americans, Asians, Eastern Europeans and Africans. Many of
them are Catholics whose impact on the church may prove as
influential as the Germans, Irish and Italians who preceded them a
century ago. Among this new group, Vietnamese are a small minority,
but their presence is hard to miss. By Gustav Niebuhr.
</P>
