<P>
   WASHINGTON WATCH VOTE CHART Questions regarding this
transmission should be directed to 202-628-3100, ext. 227.
WASHINGTON, April 21 -- The following chart shows how senators and
representatives voted on key bills and amendments within the last
week. A ``Y'' means the member voted for the measure; an ``N''
means the member voted against the measure; a ``?'' means the
member did not vote; and a ``P'' means the member voted
``present.''
</P>
<P>
   SENATE VOTES:
</P>
<P>
   1) BILL NUMBER: BUDGET
</P>
<P>
   The Senate on Thursday April 13 approved, 50-48, a five year,
1.8 trillion budget compromise for fiscal year 2001. The measure
would offer tax cuts of at least $150 billion over five years, and
as much as $215 billion if the economy continues to grow. The
budget also allocates spending for defense, education, and a
prescription drug benefit. Supporters said the budget plan would
help eliminate the national debt, provide needed tax relief, and
boost education defense and health research spending. Opponents
said the budget plan offered large tax cuts at the expense of
important social programs. A ``yes'' vote favors the budget.
</P>
<P>
   VOTE : 1
