   BKN-PLAYOFFS (Undated) _ The NBA playoffs begin on Saturday with
four games. Story will focus on key players who are hurt, among
them Tim Duncan of the San Antonio Spurs and Tim Hardaway of the
Miami Heat. By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-DEVILS (Undated) _ Follow-up on the New Jersey Devils'
four-game sweep of the Florida Panthers, which now gives New Jersey
almost a week off to bask in the accomplishment before the second
round begins. By Alex Yannis.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-TORONTO (Toronto) _ Yankees at Toronto, 4 p.m. The
Yankees' winning streak stands at eight games; Ramiro Mendoza will
try to make it nine. By Buster Olney.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-CUBS (New York) _ Chicago Cubs at Mets, 7:05 p.m. These
two teams opened the 2000 season with a two-game series in Japan in
which Bobby Valentine incurred the wrath of Don Baylor by holding
up Game 1 in the ninth inning to object to Baylor's lineup card. By
Tyler Kepner.
</P>
