u l BC-STYLE-BUDGET-NYT &LR;      04-21 0262
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STYLE-BUDGET-NYT </SLUG>
  
 Attn: Style and Leisure Editors:  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service plans the following articles
from the Style section for use Sunday, April 23, and thereafter.
</P>
<P>
   CHARLIE'S-ANGELS (Undated) _ Julia Chaplin recalls her obsession
with ``Charlie's Angels,'' the hit television series from 1976 to
1981, her pre-preteen years, about three beautiful she-detectives
who peeled around in cool sports cars and used kung fu on bad guys
even as they changed outfits a dozen times per episode, putting on
a fashion parade. Now the ``Angels'' craze is back, being fueled
primarily by a Columbia Pictures film adaptation of the television
series that will star Cameron Diaz, Lucy Liu and Drew Barrymore.
</P>
<P>
   OSCAR-KNOCKOFFS (Undated) _ Elizabeth Hayt reports on
Oscar-night fashion knockoffs, and what it feels like to wear one.
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY-FASHION (Undated) _ The Great Hockey Jersey Debate. The
agony and the ecstasy of selecting one. By Mark Lasswell.
</P>
<P>
   NITEOUT-NEMETZ (New York) _ A nite out with Brent Sterling
Nemetz, who has perfected the art of hanging from cables on the
Verrazano-Narrows Bridge and climbing backward up the ladder in the
Statue of Liberty's arm, all the while asking questions and
shooting from a Sony video camera. By Linda Lee.
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Anne Raver reports on a new book with
a catchy title, ``The New England Wild Flower Society Guide to
Growing and Propagating Wildflowers of the United States and
Canada'' (Houghton Mifflin, $40).
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUESTIONS OR RERUNS: (888) 346-9867 &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
