<TEXT>
<P>
   The Shapiro file
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, April 23.
</P>
<P>
   By Catherine Fox
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Born: 1949, New York, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Education: Bachelor's degree from Hamilton College in upstate
New York; master's degrees from Williams College in Massachusetts
and Harvard; doctorate from Harvard.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Career: Has taught at Duke University; curated at the Saint
Louis Art Museum and Atlanta's High Museum of Art; has been
director of the Los Angeles County Museum of Art; and deputy
director, acting director and director of the High Museum. He got
the top job March 28.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Family facts: Wife Lisa; children Kate, 16; and Nick, 14. His
dog is a former pound puppy named Charlie.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Favorite painting in the High: ``Lesende'' (The Reader) by
Gerhard Richter, on the third floor.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Last book he's read: ``Corelli's Mandolin'' by Louis de
Bernieres.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The music he listens to: Aaron Copland, Scott Joplin, Erik
Satie and Stravinsky.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Looking ahead: ``I think the High can become one of the
leading art museums in the country.''
</P>
<P>
   Catherine Fox writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
