<P>
   VIETNAM-MEMORIES-REVIEW (Undated) _ After serving in Vietnam we
returned home to the other Vietnam, the domestic battlefield of
hard-hats and peaceniks, the Vietnam that one side proclaimed the
frontline against godless communism and the other a symbol of all
the greed and immorality of a perfidious establishment. The
protests waned, but we still avoided talking about the war. But the
image of Vietnam and the veterans that developed in the 1980s was
far different from any Vietnam I knew. By Serge Schmemann.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in `i' category)
