   CUBA-BOY-REVIEW (Undated) _ The Elian Gonzalez case illustrates
that courts run on adult time while children suffer the
consequences. The destinies of many U.S. children remain uncertain,
sometimes for months and years, as their custody and child welfare
cases wind through the courts. Experts see tension created by two
competing notions of time: the deliberate, adult pace of the law
and the highly compressed time of child development. By Somni
Sengupta.
