<P>
   CUBAN-BOY (Washington) _ Fast running out of options, Attorney
General Janet Reno awaited word Friday from her law enforcement
agents in Miami on the best time for them to remove Elian Gonzalez
from his Florida relatives. But she could not give even his father
a timetable for their reunion. While Reno clung to hope for a
last-minute negotiated turnover, she held a surprisingly short,
15-minute meeting at the Justice Department with Juan Miguel
Gonzalez, father of the 6-year-old Cuban boy whom Miami relatives
have refused to relinquish. ``I assured him that I would continue
working toward the goal of reuniting him with his child, but I also
told him that I could not commit to a particular course of action
or timetable,'' Reno said. Justice Department officials said that
key federal marshals and immigration agents were being positioned
in Miami outside the home of Elian's great-uncle, Lazaro Gonzalez.
(Summary from wires). By David Johnston.
