investors were paying for unseasoned companies defied their
fundamental worth. The breezy days of last spring were bound, logic
said, to turn unwelcoming and cold. Still, no expert worth the
title can predict the permanence of the damage caused by the
market's recent shakeout. ``There is a herd mentality around
Internet stocks,'' says Daniel L. Rosensweig, chief executive of
ZDNet. ``Even those who professed to be long-term fundamental
investors turned out to be short-term traders.'' (Fred R.
Conrad/The New York Times)
